    "They encompass a diverse range of materials, such as bioplastics, biocomposites, biocement, myceliumbased materials, and cellulose-based materials, each with unique benefits like reduced carbon footprint, improved indoor air quality, and resource conservation (Chen et al. 2023c; Pesode and Barve 2022).",
    "However, commercial viability challenges, industry standards, and regulatory compliance must be addressed to promote widespread adoption (Niculescu and Grumezescu 2022).",
